Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil. Peel the @potato{1} and cut into 1cm thick slices. Remove the root and dark green tops from the @leek{1}, cut in half lengthways and thinly slice into half moons. Cut the @celery stick{1} lengthways into 1cm wide strips then chop into 1cm pieces. Slice the @closed cup mushrooms{1}. Pick the @thyme{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks (discard the stalks).

Add the @potato slices{1} to your pan of boiling water. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through. Be careful - you don't want the potato slices to break up too much!

Once cooked, gently drain your potato slices in a #colander{}.

Put a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Throw in the leek and celery. Cook for ~{5%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and thyme along with a pinch of salt and a grind of @black pepper{pinch}. Cook for another ~{7%minutes}.

Once the mushrooms have softened pour in the @water{100%ml}. Add the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}, bring to the boil and stir to dissolve. Add the @double cream{1}. Turn the heat to low and simmer for ~{3-5%minutes}. Add the @kale and rainbow chard mix{1/2%bag} and stir to wilt the leaves. Continue to simmer gently until the liquid has reduced by a third, another ~{5%minutes}. Take the pan off the heat.

Mix the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} with a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a #bowl{}. Crumble in the @feta cheese{1} and mix well.

Once cooked, pour the veggie mixture into an #ovenproof dish{}. Lay your potato slices on top, then sprinkle over the feta crumb and season with black pepper. Pop onto the top shelf of your oven and bake until the top is browned, ~{10%minutes}. Once your pie is ready, remove it from the oven and serve in #bowls{}. Enjoy!